do Globals.interact_with("GLOBAL_DIALOG", "Dialogic", "start")
[background arg="res://assets/bg_medbay.png" fade="0.0"]
[style name="timeline_style"]
join clone rightmost
clone: Hey.... nice to see you awake vod! \
You took a real nasty blow there. Took a while in the bacta tank to get you all better.
clone: Let's check your faculities.
label NUMBER SET
[text_input text="What's your CT number? " var="temp_value" placeholder="1234"]
if Globals.number_length() == 7.0:
	do Globals.set_player_number("temp")
	clone: Woah, a legacy number. Don't see many of those these days. Nice to see you're still around!
elif Globals.number_length() == 4.0:
	do Globals.set_player_number("temp")
	clone: Good, the blast didn't shake out all your sense.
else:
	clone: Hey, that's not funny. Your number should be something like CT-1234, or if you're a legacy trooper, CT-12-3456. This isn't time for jokes vod.
	[text_input text="What's your CT number? " var="temp_value" placeholder="12-3456"]
	if Globals.number_length()  == 7 or Globals.number_length()  == 4:
		do Globals.set_player_number("temp")
		clone: There you go...
	else:
		do Globals.set_player_number("random")
		clone: Alright... Clearly you're a bit shaken up. Your chart says your number is CT-{Globals.PlayerData["number"]}... lets move on.
label NAME SET
clone: That was an easy question. A little harder... do you rember your name?
- Yes!
	[text_input text="What's your name then vod?" var="temp_value"]
	do Globals.set_player_name("temp")
	clone: Nice to meet you {Globals.PlayerData["name"]}.
- No...
	do Globals.set_player_name("random")
	clone: That's okay, you did survive an explosion. Some stuff probably needs more time to settle. Your chart says your name is {Globals.PlayerData["name"]}. It's nice to meet you.
label GENDER SET
clone: Lets finish up this quick mental test then with one last question. What are you to me?
- Your brother
	do Globals.set_player_prnoun(0)
- Your sister
	do Globals.set_player_prnoun(1)
- Your vod
	do Globals.set_player_prnoun(2)
clone: Nice to see you are all here with us {Globals.Pronoun_Sibling[1][Globals.PlayerData["gender"]]}.\
{Globals.PlayerData["name"]} // {Globals.PlayerData["number"]}
do Globals.interact_with("GLOBAL_DIALOG", "Dialogic", "end")